          .grid_1.alpha.datestamp
            .month Jul
            .year 2012
          .grid_8.omega.content
            %h2
              A Reflection on
              %em Objects on Rails
            :maruku
              Avdi Grimm's latest book, _Objects on Rails_, is full of interesting ideas. In my opinion, it's about equally composed of interesting ideas I can't wait to try in my next project, and interesting ideas I hope I never have to work with. All of it, however, it a great starting place for discussion.
        .post
          .grid_1.alpha.datestamp
            .month Jan
            .year 2010
          .grid_8.omega.content
            %h2 Why I Love Sass: Mixins
            :maruku
              When I first started using a lot of CSS3 features in my layouts, I quickly got tired of declaring everything in three different ways. Enter Sass, and the magic of mixins.
        .post
          .grid_1.alpha.datestamp
            .month Feb
            .year 2009
          .grid_8.omega.content
            %h2 Split Using Regular Expressions
            :maruku
              I just ran into a really interesting results playing around in IRB, and a few Google searches turn up no other mentions. When you split a string, you can use a regular expression as your split delimiter. That's pretty handy. But what happens when you have a capture group in that regular expression?
